			<div class="content" id="post-content-4836292">
									

<p>If your clientele are vampires who stopped paying attention to popular culture centuries before Bram Stoker was born, why would they associate Transylvania with vampires specifically, let alone care that other people do?</p>
<p>So far as I am aware, vampires only became associated with the borderlands between Hungary and Romania as a result of <em>Dracula</em>; vampire-like creatures are a pretty universal phenomenon in folklore, but vampires-as-vampires date from the 18th century in Eastern Europe more broadly.</p>

